I'm going to try to go again on Saturday. The weather isn't terrible right now, but it's only Monday.
The difficulties are already starting to appear. I will probably have a lot of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it's going to take an ENORMOUS amount of time and require a LOT of extra work.
Even if it's discouraging, it's just one more problem to solve and, for now, it seems *totally* manageable. It's just that it's going to take a lot of time and $$$$.
In case the challenge that awaits me interests you.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. It does not issue a medical certificate if you're receiving treatment for that.
